snippet.textDisplay:
I feel so proud of this man- as a fellow Brit, I truly believe he has elevated the sport and hope the visions he laid out in this video would be realised one day.
On a sad note, it is rather glaring the misconceptions that the media helps to propagate against him. Which begs the question why? I remember during his very early years how the likes of Martin Brundle would use their privileged positions and question his mental faculty and at the same time heap praises on the likes of Rosberg about their intelligence and thinking capacity.
I believed then and still do now these were the building stones for the hate that is generated towards Hamilton to this day as most of his haters would put it down to him being given a helping hand when the fact is truly the opposite.
I know most would doubt this but if they ought to go through the archives of the commentaries on these races in full and get my point.
They always used terms like aggressive and brain in such veiled way but whenever another driver displayed worst they would explain it away- most recently is the rather arrogant and frankly rude attitude of Verstappen- listen to the deafening sound of silence about his mannerisms.


I wish Hamilton and Mercedes a very successful and harmonious 2020 and may the fans be better for it...


P.S... You must finish your career in Red! :)

snippet.textDisplay:
Watching Lewis grow as a driver & person over the years has been a complete honour & absolute pleasure. People seem to forget he wasn't always as dominant as he is now, there were times when almost anything he did on track received penalties from the stewards. I personally believe this helped him mature & grow into the force he is now & his dominance is a direct result of those times. Huge respect has to go to anybody who can take those knocks & learn from them.
I remember watching Schumacher win his championships & claiming all his records, never did I think I'd be lucky enough to see another legend of the sport rise & surpass the achievements of the most successful driver of all time. I genuinely believed that nobody would ever come close, but here we are, on the brink of seeing that happen.
It's been so incredible to watch you rise over the last 12 years Lewis & I honestly feel blessed to have witnessed the 2 most successful drivers of all time (I'm also old enough to have watched the careers of senna & prost). Yes everyone has their favourite drivers past & present, but stats don't lie. I look forward to seeing you race over the next few years & watching you claim those final few records. Then there can be no doubters, you ARE the greatest of all time !!!
You're an inspiration & fantastic role model for present & future generations. Keep doing what you do & simply being you dude. Big love 💕
